-- Harrison Twins Commit to College Basketball at Champion Kentucky
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-10-05T04:01:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-04/top-rated-harrison-twins-to-play-college-basketball-at-kentucky.html
Twins Andrew and Aaron Harrison,
rated as two of the top high school basketball players in the
country, committed to play at the University of Kentucky.  Andrew is the top point guard while Aaron is the top-rated
shooting guard in the country, according to ESPN’s ratings.  The Harrisons, who go to Travis High School in Richmond,
Texas, chose coach  John Calipari ’s team over the University of
Maryland and  Southern Methodist University . Kentucky won the
national championship last season.  “We liked coach Caliperi’s fire to win and we want to win
a national championship,” Andrew said last night after his
decision was announced.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
